s written to the women’s pages in agricultural newspapers, they forged a vital network that supported, encouraged and educated women in ways to improve their rural lives. Their letters show how these rural women made significant and vital contributions to the settlement and development of the Canadian North-West.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aRural womenxCorrespondencexCanada, Northern. 0aRural womenxCorrespondencexCanada, Western. 0aRural womenzCanada, NorthernvCorrespondence. 0aRural womenzCanada, NorthernxCorrespondence. 0aRural womenzCanada, WesternvCorrespondence. 0aRural womenzCanada, WesternxCorrespondence. 0aWomen pioneersxCorrespondencexCanada, Northern. 0aWomen pioneersxCorrespondencexCanada, Western. 0aWomen pioneerszCanada, NorthernvCorrespondence. 0aWomen pioneerszCanada, NorthernxCorrespondence. 0aWomen pioneerszCanada, WesternvCorrespondence. 0aWomen pioneerszCanada, WesternxCorrespondence. 4aBiography & Autobiography. 4aHistory: Canadian History. 4aLife Writing. 4aSocial Science: Women’s Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh1 aLewis, Norah L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978088920732540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889207325423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889207325/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles